videos.description: After taking a 3-0 lead on the opening drive, Pittsburgh fumbles on the kickoff and Virginia Tech recovers. The Hokies would be stopped short and have to settle for a field goal to expand the lead to 6-0.
videos.headline: Pitt fumbles on the kickoff to help Virginia Tech expand lead

videos.description: Nathan Peterman pass intercepted Mook Reynolds return for no gain to the Pitt 29
videos.headline: N. Peterman pass intercepted, M. Reynolds return  for 0 yds

videos.description: Virginia Tech goes deep to Isaiah Ford but the ball bounces around off of Phillipie Motley as both players fall to the ground before Ford finally corrals it in for the wild completion.
videos.headline: Ball pinballs into a wild Virginia Tech catch

videos.description: Pittsburgh has struggled all night on offense until James Conner caps off an 84-yard drive with a six-yard run up the middle to cut Virginia Tech's lead to 9-7.
videos.headline: Connor goes up the middle for TD, cuts into Hokies' lead

videos.description: After squandering a number of red zone chances earlier in the game, Virginia Tech finally gets into the end zone when Jerod Evans hits Chris Cunningham for an 11-yard touchdown to increase the Hokies' lead at 16-7.
videos.headline: Virginia Tech finally finds the end zone with Evans' pass to Cunningham

videos.description: James Conner run for 1 yd for a TD
videos.headline: J. Conner run for 1 yd for a TD

videos.description: James Conner plows through the line and into the end zone from one-yard out, his third score of the game, putting Pittsburgh up for the first time at 21-16.
videos.headline: Conner scores his third TD of the night

videos.description: Jerod Evans run for a loss of 1 yard to the Pitt 9
videos.headline: Virginia Tech quarterback Jerod Evans injured on play

videos.description: After struggling in the red zone all night, Virginia Tech gets back into the end zone again when Marshawn Williams gets hit short but fights his way to the goal line, increasing the Hokies' lead at 29-21.
videos.headline: Williams refuses to be denied the end zone for another Hokies touchdown

videos.description: Brian O'Neill, an offensive lineman, take the handoff and sweeps right to dive for the end zone and scores for Pitt. The Panthers would add the two-point conversion to tie the game at 29-29.
videos.headline: Offensive lineman takes handoff and dives for Pitt TD

videos.description: N. Peterman pass  to J. Conner for Two-Point Conversion
videos.headline: N. Peterman pass  to J. Conner for Two-Point Conversion

videos.description: Isaiah Ford makes history with a school record 23rd receiving touchdown and does it in style with a spinning, juggling catch to increase the Hokies' lead in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Ford's juggling catch is a record breaker for Virginia Tech

videos.description: Trailing by 10 points, Nathan Peterman finds Jester Weah for the touchdown to keep Pittsburgh alive and cut the lead to 39-36.
videos.headline: Pitt not going away yet when Peterman hits Weah for TD
